In a given folder (folder contains files, subfolders or empty) to find
duplicate (in content) files. Application should use multithreading.
When application finds a duplicate pair, filenames of this files are
written to results file.  Use of separate thread (not main thread) for
writing results is required. Duplicate pairs should be written as soon as
they are found - not when exiting the application.
There should be an ability (from interface) to stop, restart and continue
search and writer threads.

Program input: path to folder, name of results file, search thread count.
Program output:  results file.


You can use either C/C++/C#/Java or any other language of your choice
(please write me about language you want to use first (if it is not on the
list))



Operating system: Windows or Linux

